From The New York Times, 15 April 1919:

&quot;The Atlantic Fleet, with the new superdreadnought Mississippi leading the way, steamed in stately column into the Hudson yesterday, its unexpected arrival being just twenty hours ahead of the schedule announced two weeks ago by the Navy Department.&quot;

